description.plain:
AlunaGeorge is a British club-soul duo, composed of vocalist Aluna Francis and producer George Reid. The two first met when  George remixed “Sweetheart” by Aluna’s first band, My Toys Like Me. Their first single, “You Know You Like It,” was released in 2012, followed by the full-length LP Body Music the following year. Their sophomore album, I Remember, followed in 2016.

The duo are well-known for their extensive collaborations with other electronic artists, including tracks with KAYTRANADA, Baauer, Take Ü There, Avicii, Flume, and Disclosure.

description.plain:
“You Know You Like it” is the lead single to AlunaGeorge’s debut album, Body Music. It achieved moderate success in the UK and helped further established the duo in its scene.

It’s about being yourself, being that person on the dance floor that’s making a fool out of themselves, but having a good time. And then saying to the person in the corner that’s like “Idiot”: “Come on, you love it, you’re watching me.”

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FWR9MR5juWI



In 2014, DJ Snake remixed the song as his own single, introducing the song to an American audience.

songs.full_title: I'm In Control by AlunaGeorge (Ft. Popcaan)
songs.title: I’m In Control

description.plain:
“I’m in Control” is the lead single from the AlunaGeorge’s  sophomore album I Remember.
Jamaican star Popcaan lends his dancehall credentials to the British electronic pop duo in this song about women being in charge.

 Billboard wrote: ”'I’m in Control' demands intellectual prowess from prospective suitors.”

“I’m In Control”  incorporates slightly more live instrumentation than the songs on AlunaGeorge’s debut album Body Music, a goal George Reid kept in mind while producing its follow-up to avoid getting “lost in a world in a synths.”

The track premiered as Annie Mac’s Hottest Record In The World on January 20, 2016.

songs.title: Not Above Love

description.plain:
“Not Above Love” got its premiere on BBC Radio 1 with Annie Mac.

Aluna had this to say during her interview with Annie:

I think this song speaks for itself, it was a moment where I was really stuck in this emotional… that point where you keep going round and round and you can’t snap out of it and a friend of mine really just explained to me that this person was promising things but not actually delivering anything and they were just stealing my obsessive energy that I was giving to that person.

The song samples “Plan B” by Slow Motion Centerfold.
